        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Tumor localization according to the ICD10-CM classification.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Depth_of_Invasion_8Edition -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Depth_of_Invasion_8Edition">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Indicates the depth range for tumor invasion in the oral cavity. Extracted from TNM 8th edition.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Extension_to_lingual_surface_of_epiglottis_is_present -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Extension_to_lingual_surface_of_epiglottis_is_present">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Indicates whether or not the epiglottis is extended to the lingual surface in a tumor located in the oropharynx.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Laterality_of_T -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Laterality_of_T">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Indicates the side of the body where the tumor is located. The possible options can be: left, right and midline.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#N_Side -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#N_Side">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Indicates the position of the involved lymph nodes in relation to the primary tumor. The possible options can be: ipsilateral, contralateral and bilateral.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Node_Levels_Left -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Node_Levels_Left">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Localization in left side of body, of the involved lymph nodes based on the lymph node levels of the neck.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Node_Levels_Right -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Node_Levels_Right">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Localization in right side of body, of the involved lymph nodes based on the lymph node levels of the neck.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Notes_ctn -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Notes_ctn">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Stage_at_Diagnosis_7Edition -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Stage_at_Diagnosis_7Edition">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Prognostic stage groups are assigned based on disease site-specific T, N, and M categories and relevant prognostic factors to group patients with similar prognosis and/or treatment approach. Indicates the stage group based on the AJCC 7th edition. 

The stage is calculated as follows:
Stage 0 = Tis - N0 - M0
Stage I = T1 - N0 - M0
Stage II = T2 - N0 - M0
Stage III = T3 - N0 - M0
                 T1 - N1 - M0
                 T2 - N1 - M0
                 T3 - N1 - M0
Stage IVA = T4a - N0 - M0
                   T4a - N1 - M0
                   T1 - N2 - M0
                   T2 - N2 - M0
                   T3 - N2 - M0
                   T4a - N2 - M0
Stage IVB = Any T - N3 (7th Ed.)/N3a,b (8th Ed.) - M0 
                   T4b - Any N - M0
Stage IVC = Any T - Any N - M1</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Stage_at_Diagnosis_8Edition_OralCavity_Oropharynx_p16Negative_Hypopharynx_Larynx -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Stage_at_Diagnosis_8Edition_OralCavity_Oropharynx_p16Negative_Hypopharynx_Larynx">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Prognostic stage groups are assigned based on disease site-specific T, N, and M categories and relevant prognostic factors to group patients with similar prognosis and/or treatment approach. Indicates the stage group based on the AJCC 8th edition for Oral Cavity, Oropharynx (p16-Negative), Hypopharynx and Larynx. 

The stage is calculated as follows:
Stage 0 = Tis - N0 - M0
Stage I = T1 - N0 - M0
Stage II = T2 - N0 - M0
Stage III = T3 - N0 - M0
                 T1 - N1 - M0
                 T2 - N1 - M0
                 T3 - N1 - M0
Stage IVA = T4a - N0 - M0
                   T4a - N1 - M0
                   T1 - N2 - M0
                   T2 - N2 - M0
                   T3 - N2 - M0
                   T4a - N2 - M0
Stage IVB = Any T - N3 (7th Ed.)/N3a,b (8th Ed.) - M0 
                   T4b - Any N - M0
Stage IVC = Any T - Any N - M1</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Stage_at_Diagnosis_8Edition_Oropharynx_p16Positive -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Stage_at_Diagnosis_8Edition_Oropharynx_p16Positive">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Prognostic stage groups are assigned based on disease site-specific T, N, and M categories and relevant prognostic factors to group patients with similar prognosis and/or treatment approach. Indicates the stage group based on the AJCC 8th edition for Oropharynx (p16-Positive). 

The stage is calculated as follows:
Stage 0 = Tis - N0 - M0
Stage I = T1 - N0 - M0
               T2 - N0 - M0
               T1 - N1 - M0
               T2 - N1 - M0
Stage II = T3 - N0 - M0
                T3 - N1 - M0
                T1 - N2 - M0
                T2 - N2 - M0
                T3 - N2 - M0
Stage III = Any T - N3 - M0
                 T4 - Any N - M0
Stage IV = Any T - Any N - M1</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#T4_Oral_Cavity_classified_as_such_for_only_bone_erosion -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#T4_Oral_Cavity_classified_as_such_for_only_bone_erosion">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Indicates whether or not there is bone erosion in a tumor located in the oral cavity.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cN_7Edition -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cN_7Edition">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cN_8Edition_OralCavity_Oropharynx_p16Negative_Hypopharynx_Larynx -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cN_8Edition_OralCavity_Oropharynx_p16Negative_Hypopharynx_Larynx">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cN_8Edition_Oropharynx_p16Positive -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cN_8Edition_Oropharynx_p16Positive">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Method used to determine the grade of a tumor for Oropharynx cancer p-16 positive (HPV positive) patients.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cT_7Edition -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cT_7Edition">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Neoplasm Staging - Methods which attempt to express in replicable terms the extent of the neoplasm in the patient.
The TNM staging system  is a system to describe the amount and spread of cancer in a patient’s body, using TNM. T describes the size of the tumor and any spread of cancer into nearby tissue; N describes spread of cancer to nearby lymph nodes; and M describes metastasis (spread of cancer to other parts of the body). This system was created and is updated by the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) and the International Union Against Cancer (UICC). The TNM staging system is used to describe most types of cancer. Also called AJCC staging system.
This refer to the 7th edition published in 2009 and the effective dates for cancer diagnoses are 2010-2016.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cT_8Edition_OralCavity_Oropharynx_p16Negative_Hypopharynx_Larynx -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cT_8Edition_OralCavity_Oropharynx_p16Negative_Hypopharynx_Larynx">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The TNM staging system is a system to describe the amount and spread of cancer in a patient’s body, using TNM. T describes the size of the tumor and any spread of cancer into nearby tissue; N describes spread of cancer to nearby lymph nodes; and M describes metastasis (spread of cancer to other parts of the body). This system was created and is updated by the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) and the International Union Against Cancer (UICC). The TNM staging system is used to describe most types of cancer. Also called AJCC staging system.
This refer to the 8th edition published in 2016 and the effective dates for cancer diagnoses are from 2017.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cT_8Edition_Oropharynx_p16Positive -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cT_8Edition_Oropharynx_p16Positive">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Tissue_Invasion_ExtraNodalExtension -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Tissue_Invasion_ExtraNodalExtension">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Invasion refers to the direct extension and penetration by cancer cells into neighbouring tissues. Indicates whether or not the tumor has spread beyond the outer margin of a lymph node.  Extra-capsular extension of nodal tumor.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Tissue_Invasion_ExtraNodalExtension_to -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Tissue_Invasion_ExtraNodalExtension_to">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Indicates which tissue have been invaded by the tumor once has spread beyond the outer margin of lymph node. The possible invaded tissues can be: skin, muscle, cranial nerve XI, brachial plexus and parotid gland.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Tumor_Region -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#Tumor_Region">
        <owl:equivalentClass rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/population/HRSctn#Site"/>
        <owl:equivalentClass rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/population/PSctn#Topography"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D#Clinical_T_and_N_Characteristics"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Anatomical site of a tumor, where the tumor is localized.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </owl:Class>
    


