    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cN_8Edition_Oropharynx_p16Positive@@3">
        <rdfs:label>N1</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Alphanumeric code of the TNM classification system (8th Edition) which in this case indicates that the oropharynx cancer (p16-Positive) has spread to one or more ipsilateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:comment>One or more ipsilateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm</rdfs:comment>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cN_8Edition_Oropharynx_p16Positive@@4">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Alphanumeric code of the TNM classification system (8th Edition) which in this case indicates that the oropharynx cancer (p16-Positive) has spread to contralateral or bilateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>N2</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Contralateral or bilateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm</rdfs:comment>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/ctn#TNM_cN_8Edition_Oropharynx_p16Positive@@5">
        <rdfs:label>N3</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Alphanumeric code of the TNM classification system (8th Edition) which in this case indicates that the oropharynx cancer (p16-Positive) has spread to one or more lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:comment>Lymph node(s), larger than 6 cm</rdfs:comment>
    </rdf:Description>
