    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/radio#Setting@@1">
        <rdfs:comment>Radiotherapy is the main treatment</rdfs:comment>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Radiotherapy configuration in which radiotherapy is the main treatment.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Definitive</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/radio#Setting@@2">
        <rdfs:comment>Radiotherapy is performed after surgery</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>Postoperative</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Radiotherapy configuration in which radiotherapy is perforomed after surgery.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/radio#Target_Volume_RT@@1">
        <rdfs:label>GTVT (definitive cases only)</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Gross Target Volume of the primary tumor. Selected when only the primary tumor is irradiated.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/radio#Target_Volume_RT@@2">
        <rdfs:label>GTVN (definitive cases only)</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Gross Target Volume of positive lymph nodes. Selected when only lymph nodes are irradiated.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/radio#Target_Volume_RT@@3">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Global gross target Volume including primary tumor and lymph nodes. Selected when both primary tumor and lymph nodes are irradiated.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>total GTV (definitive cases only)</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/radio#Type_of_RT@@1">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A procedure that uses a computer to create a 3-dimensional picture of the tumor. This allows doctors to give the highest possible dose of radiation to the tumor, while sparing the normal tissue as much as possible. Also called 3-dimensional conformal radiation therapy and 3-dimensional radiation therapy.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>3D-RT</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/radio#Type_of_RT@@2">
        <rdfs:label>Conventional IMRT</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Intensity-modulated radiation therapy: a type of 3-dimensional radiation therapy that uses computer-generated images to show the size and shape of the tumor. Thin beams of radiation of different intensities are aimed at the tumor from many angles. This type of radiation therapy reduces the damage to healthy tissue near the tumor. Also called IMRT.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/radio#Type_of_RT@@3">
        <rdfs:label>VMAT</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/radio#Type_of_RT@@4">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A type of therapy in which radiation is aimed at a tumor from many different directions. The patient lays on a table and is moved through a donut-shaped machine. The radiation source in the machine rotates around the patient in a spiral pattern. Before radiation, a 3-dimensional (3-D) image of the tumor is taken. This helps doctors find the highest dose of radiation that can be used to kill tumor cells while causing less damage to nearby tissue. Tomotherapy is a type of intensity-modulated radiation therapy (IMRT). Also called helical tomotherapy.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Tomotherapy</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/risk#Alcohol_at_Time_of_Diagnosis">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>An indication of a person&apos;s current alcohol consumption as well as some indication of alcohol consumption history.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
