    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Kind_of_Left_Neck_Dissection@@3">
        <rdfs:label>Radical</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Kind_of_Left_Neck_Dissection@@4">
        <rdfs:label>Sentinel node biopsy</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Removal and examination of the sentinel node(s) (the first lymph node(s) to which cancer cells are likely to spread from a primary tumor). To identify the sentinel lymph node(s), the surgeon injects a radioactive substance, blue dye, or both near the tumor. The surgeon then uses a probe to find the sentinel lymph node(s) containing the radioactive substance or looks for the lymph node(s) stained with dye. The surgeon then removes the sentinel node(s) to check for the presence of cancer cells.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Kind_of_Right_Neck_Dissection@@1">
        <rdfs:label>Selective</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Kind_of_Right_Neck_Dissection@@2">
        <rdfs:label>Modified Radical</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Kind_of_Right_Neck_Dissection@@3">
        <rdfs:label>Radical</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Kind_of_Right_Neck_Dissection@@4">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Removal and examination of the sentinel node(s) (the first lymph node(s) to which cancer cells are likely to spread from a primary tumor). To identify the sentinel lymph node(s), the surgeon injects a radioactive substance, blue dye, or both near the tumor. The surgeon then uses a probe to find the sentinel lymph node(s) containing the radioactive substance or looks for the lymph node(s) stained with dye. The surgeon then removes the sentinel node(s) to check for the presence of cancer cells</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Sentinel node biopsy</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Method_of_Surgery@@1">
        <rdfs:label>Open/Conventional surgery</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Method_of_Surgery@@2">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A surgical procedure that uses the cutting power of a laser beam to make bloodless cuts in tissue or to remove a surface lesion such as a tumor.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Laser surgery</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Neck_Dissection@@1">
        <rdfs:label>No</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Neck_Dissection@@2">
        <rdfs:label>Yes</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Plan_of_Care_Modified_by_Complication@@1">
        <rdfs:label>No</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Plan_of_Care_Modified_by_Complication@@2">
        <rdfs:label>Yes</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Site_Neck_Dissection@@1">
        <rdfs:label>Right</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Site_Neck_Dissection@@2">
        <rdfs:label>Left</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Site_Neck_Dissection@@3">
        <rdfs:label>Bilateral</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Site_of_Surgery@@1">
        <rdfs:label>Left</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Site_of_Surgery@@2">
        <rdfs:label>Right</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Site_of_Surgery@@3">
        <rdfs:label>Midline</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Surgery_Reason@@1">
        <rdfs:label>Primary Tumor</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A term used to describe the original, or first, tumor in the body. Cancer cells from a primary cancer may spread to other parts of the body and form new, or secondary, tumors. This is called metastasis. These secondary tumors are the same type of cancer as the primary cancer. Also called primary tumor.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Surgery_Reason@@2">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Cancer that has recurred (come back), usually after a period of time during which the cancer could not be detected. The cancer may come back to the same place as the original (primary) tumor or to another place in the body. Also called recurrent cancer.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Recurrence</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Surgery_Reason@@3">
        <rdfs:label>Other</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Surgical_Reconstruction@@1">
        <rdfs:label>Free flaps</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>There is no direct blood connection by local vessels or locally surgically connected vessels</rdfs:comment>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgical reconstruction technique in which the removed tissue has no direct blood connection by local vessels or locally surgically connected vessels while being transferred.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Surgical_Reconstruction@@2">
        <rdfs:label>Graft</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Healthy skin, bone, or other tissue taken from one part of the body and used to replace diseased or injured tissue removed from another part of the body.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Surgical_Reconstruction@@3">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgical reconstruction technique in which the local tissue next to the removed tissue is used for reconstruction.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Local flaps</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>The local tissue next to the removed tissue is used for reconstrucion</rdfs:comment>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Surgical_Reconstruction@@4">
        <rdfs:label>Loco-Regional flaps</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgical reconstruction technique in which the local and connected tissue of the region is used for reconstruction.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:comment>The local and connected tissue of the region is used for reconstruction</rdfs:comment>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Surgical_Reconstruction@@5">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Type of surgical reconstruction in which the wound/defect is either directly closed or left open for primary wound healing (e.g. laser surgery od the larynx). No reconstrucion by grafts and/or flaps is performed.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Primary closure</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>No reconstrucion by grafts and/or flaps is performed. The wound/defect is either directly closed or left open for primary wound healing (e.g. laser surgery od the larynx)</rdfs:comment>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Tracheostomy@@1">
        <rdfs:label>No</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Tracheostomy@@2">
        <rdfs:label>Yes</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Complication@@1">
        <rdfs:label>Wound infection</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Complication@@2">
        <rdfs:label>Intraoperative hemorrhage</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Complication@@3">
        <rdfs:label>Postoperative hemorrhage</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Complication@@4">
        <rdfs:label>Wound complication</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Complication@@5">
        <rdfs:label>Wound dehiscence</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Complication@@6">
        <rdfs:label>Skin loss</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Loss of skin during or mostly after a surgical procedure.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Complication@@7">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Necrosis of a flap during or mostly after surgery due to infection, local  thrombosis, loss of perfusion or adaption or for other reasons.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Flap necrosis</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Complication@@8">
        <rdfs:label>Fistula</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>An abnormal opening or passage between two organs or between an organ and the surface of the body. Fistulas may be caused by injury, infection, or inflammation, or may be created during surgery.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Complication@@9">
        <rdfs:label>Other</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@1">
        <rdfs:label>Glossectomy</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgerical procedure that removes parts of the tongue or even the whole organ.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@10">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgery that removes parts of the floor of the mouth.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Surgery –Floor of the mouth</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@11">
        <rdfs:label>Total Laryngectomy</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Total surgical removement of the larynx.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@12">
        <rdfs:label>Resection</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@13">
        <rdfs:label>Other</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@2">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgery that removes parts of the larynx and pharynx or even the whole organ (in case of the larynx).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Laryngopharyngectomy</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@3">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgery that removes parts of/the whole mandibula.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Mandibulectomy</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@4">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgery that removes parts of the maxilla.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Maxillectomy</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@5">
        <rdfs:label>Oropharyngeal resection with mandible split/reconstruction</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgery that removes parts of the oropharynx with a reconstruction of the mandibula.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@6">
        <rdfs:label>Oropharyngeal tumor resection</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgery that removes parts of the oropharynx.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@7">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgery that removes parts of the larynx but not the whole organ.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Partial laryngeal resection</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@8">
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgery that removes parts of the pharynx.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>Pharyngectomy</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.lst.tfo.upm.es/BD2D/surge#Type_of_Surgery@@9">
        <rdfs:label>Surgery – Orbital Floor Resection</rdfs:label>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Surgery that removes at least parts of the orbital floor or even the whole structure.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    </rdf:Description>
